  "text": "For v ∈ B H , define and denote by I (H,S) the ideal of L K (E) generated by H ∪ {v H | v ∈ S}. According to [CITATION_1] Theorem 5.7] , all the graded ideals of a Leavitt path algebra L K (E) are of the form I (H,S) for a suitable pair (H, S), being H a hereditary and saturated subset of vertices of E 0 .",
